casebody.data:
No. 22,

Original.

State of Tennessee v. State of Arkansas et al. Argued on motion to dismiss April 14, 1919. Decided April 21, 1919. Mr. Barnette E. Moses and Mr. Frank M. Thompson for plaintiff. Mr. W. J. Lamb and Mr. Skipwith Adams for defendants. Per Curiam.

Bill dismissed with costs for want of equity, on the authority of Jackson v. United States, 230 U. S. 1; Hughes v. United States, 230 U. S. 24, and Cubbins v. Mississippi River Commission, 241 U. S. 351.
